Welcome to The FCC source code disk.

     I (The Hitchhiker) have decided to quit The FCC and give 
away the source code that I wrote for them.  There are only 8 
FCC disks at present, and here is the code for all of them.  The 
actual menus are written in HiSoft BASIC, but should compile 
with Power BASIC and FirST BASIC, both from HiSoft.
     
     Also on this disk is a program that I developed that allows 
data files (or pictures) to be included in the BASIC program 
listing.  Code programmers can use 'incbin' but BASIC has no way 
of including data.  This program converts a file into a series 
of DATA statements that can be used in the program.  It will 
also slightly compress the data.  The BASIC file DECRUNCH.BAS 
must be included in any program that uses the data statements.

     Well I hope that you enjoy looking through the listings on 
this disk, it really shows what HiSoft BASIC is capable of.

NOTE FOR THE MONSTER:  Sorry about this Neil, now you'll have to 
write your own menus, if you can...!

     There are a few FCC disks (number 5+) that contain a few 
bugs, I would like to say that I had nothing to do with these 
disks, The Monster started pissing about with my code, and 
couldn't be bothered to fully test the menus.

     Look out for **THE REVENGE**, coming very soon to an ATARI 
ST near you.  We intend to do the most thorough utility packs yet 
on the ST, if not any computer.


THE HITCHHIKER of The Revenge 5th May 1990
